# Coracobrachialis

> The **coracobrachialis** is a slender muscle of the medial arm, connecting the [[Coracoid Process]] to the medial humerus. It assists in shoulder flexion and adduction.

## 🔗 Key Connections
- **Origin** — [[Coracoid Process]] of [[Scapula]] (with short head of [[Biceps Brachii]])
- **Insertion** — Medial surface of [[Humerus]] (midshaft)
- **Nerve** — [[Musculocutaneous Nerve]] (C5, C6, C7) — penetrates coracobrachialis
- **Action** — Shoulder flexion + adduction

## 🏥 Clinical Significance
- **Musculocutaneous nerve** — Pierces through the coracobrachialis; entrapment here is rare but possible
- **Coracobrachialis hypertrophy** — Can compress musculocutaneous nerve

